# Security

## Trust Zones

- Launcher host environment.
- Generated project filesystem.
- External services (`gh`, remote APIs).
- Agent CLI invocation boundary.

## Forbidden Patterns

- Unbounded shell interpolation of model output.
- Unvalidated path execution.
- Echoing secrets to stdout, stderr, or generated files.
- Auto-applied diffs without human approval.

## Auth and Transport

- Auth profiles: `none`, `local-token`, `mtls`, `oauth`.
- HTTP transport requires TLS.
- `stdio` transport restricted to local sockets with file permission checks.

## Secrets

- Sourced from environment variables or platform keychain only.
- Never persisted to generated project files.
- Redacted in logs by `scripts/lib/log.sh`.

## Threat Review

Adding any new external integration or any MCP tool that mutates external
state requires a threat review and an explicit policy entry.
